Describe an activity that made you feel tired.
- when and where it happened
- why you took part in it
- what the activity was
- explain why it made you feel tired

I’d like to talk about a badminton match I played with a group of close friends a few months ago, which left me feeling completely exhausted but also really satisfied.

It took place on a Saturday morning at a park near our neighborhood. We usually meet there on weekends to play badminton as a way to stay active and unwind after a busy week. However, on that particular day, we decided to make things more exciting by turning our usual game into a friendly competition. The winning team would be treated to a meal at a restaurant of their choice.

There were four of us, divided into two teams, and the match quickly became much more intense than we had expected. Everyone was highly competitive and determined to win, so we ended up playing several rounds in a row. We were constantly running, jumping, and smashing the shuttlecock with full energy.

What made it especially tiring was the fact that we played for hours under the hot summer sun. By the end of the match, I was completely worn out, both physically and mentally. I could barely catch my breath, and my muscles felt sore.

Fortunately, my teammate and I managed to win, which made all the effort worthwhile. Later that evening, we went out for a meal together to celebrate, and it turned into a really enjoyable and memorable experience.

Overall, even though the match was exhausting, it brought us closer as friends and motivated us to stay active. In fact, we decided to make it a monthly tradition, which I’m really looking forward to.
